column30:
When customers have multiple external calendars connected (Google/Outlook/etc.), the scheduler hides any time slot marked as “busy” on _any_ connected calendar. However, the system does not surface which calendar or event caused the block. This makes troubleshooting difficult.

Im not sure how accurate this is (yes I asked AI), but could there be some debug parameter added:

*Add a debug parameter to* {{get-availability}}

{noformat}GET /get-availability?debug=true{noformat}

This could return something like:

{noformat}{
  "success": true,
  "available": ["2025-12-16T16:00:00Z", ...],
  "blocked": [
     {
       "start": "2025-12-16T16:00:00Z",
       "reason": "Google Calendar — Customer Service",
       "event_title": "Team Meeting"
     }
  ]
}{noformat}

Even a simple:

{noformat}"blockedBy": "Google: Customer Service"{noformat}

The customer saw this message

{quote}“Processed 3,710 contacts: 692 added, 18 skipped (except for tags)”)
doesn’t clearly explain what happens to the thousands of records that *matched existing contacts*.{quote}

But having the language say something like this might be more helpful

{quote}“Processed 3,710 contacts – 692 new, 3,000 matched existing records, 18 not added due to suppressed or invalid data.”{quote}

Alternatively, some sort of ‘version control’ or ‘import summary diff’ would be cool too.

Thought it might be fun to have a way for clients to attach this to their page in some way. Side nav (or a pop up) could control the particles, angle, speed etc etc. 

Lets users gamify things a little. 

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
Editor page: [https://attractwell.com/app/pages/edit/39012|https://attractwell.com/app/pages/edit/39012]
{panel}

The cover photo image in the discussion room is ‘chopping’ the image off. Theres no option to ‘show entire photo' like there is with the vault setup section.

To solve this, I needed to use the about me section and force the image with some CSS. Also bootstrap played a little bit of havoc on me. This is what I got so far:

{noformat}<style>

#member-area-header > div {
  padding: 0px !important;
  margin: 0px !important;
  width: 100% !important;
}

body > div.hidden-sm.hidden-md.hidden-lg.container.notopmargin.container-fullwidth {
  padding: 0px !important;
  margin: 0px !important;
}

</style>{noformat}
